U.K. Stocks Resume Retreat; FTSE 100 Declines 0.5 Percent

-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-08-09T07:29:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/u-k-stocks-resume-retreat-ftse-100-declines-0-5-percent.html
U.K. stocks resumed their retreat,
sending the FTSE 100 Index down for an eighth day.  The benchmark gauge lost 0.5 percent to 5,043.16 at 8:26
a.m. in  London  after earlier rallying 1 percent.  Tate & Lyle Plc (TATE) , Vodafone Group Plc and BP Plc pced
declining shares, all falling at least 1.9 percent in London
trading.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
